# IoT-Based Hand Gesture Recognition and Control System Using ESP32

## Overview

This project enables wireless control of electrical devices using hand gestures. An ESP32 microcontroller processes sensor data and communicates with connected devices through IoT technology, allowing real-time monitoring and control.

## Features

* Hand gesture recognition for device control
* Wireless communication using ESP32
* Real-time monitoring and automation
* Low-cost and user-friendly implementation
* IoT-based remote accessibility

## Components Used

* ESP32 Development Board
* MPU6050 Accelerometer and Gyroscope Sensor
* Relay Module
* LEDs / Electrical Loads
* Jumper Wires
* Breadboard
* Power Supply

## Working Principle

1. The MPU6050 sensor detects hand movements and gestures.
2. Sensor data is processed by the ESP32.
3. Specific gestures are mapped to control commands.
4. Commands are sent to connected devices through relay modules.
5. Devices are turned ON/OFF based on recognized gestures.

